title: Backbone: Fixed History.Started being undefined
body: The History.started flag is set on the class rather than on the class instance (as it is set once globally). Attempts to read _Backbone.history.started_ (via the global history instance) always return undefined. Instead the typing should be static member (_Backbone.History.started_ is where the correct value is located). This can be seen at http://backbonejs.org/docs/backbone.html#section-203

- moved the `declare module` part into the `jquery-module.d.ts` file
- the main `jquery.d.ts` includes a `jquery-base.d.ts` part plus the module definition and global vars. This is for backwards compatibility.
- the `jquery-base.d.ts` is the old `jquery.d.ts` without the global declarations.

The point of this PR is to be able to use jQuery with a module loader without the `$` and `jQuery` globals.
